added.title: Point to the Plaza
added.description: When a Gloop infestation takes over the plaza, Point arrives to contain the situation.

added.title: Red Action to the Future
added.description: When Red Action is called to the future for an epic battle, Enid is unsure of what to do.

added.title: Wisdom, Strength, and Charisma
added.description: When Enid goes to a new school, KO sets out to make sure she fits in.

added.title: Let's Be Heroes
added.description: When KO tags along with his mom to work, he discovers the convenience store next door is his key to becoming a great hero.

added.title: Let's Be Friends
added.description: KO wants to become friends with Enid and Rad and get hired at Lakewood Plaza Turbo.

added.title: We Messed Up
added.description: KO, Rad and Enid accidentally break one of Mr. Gar's prized possessions!

added.title: You Get Me
added.description: Enid gets turned to stone, and it's up to KO to turn her back to normal.

added.title: Midnight Madness
added.description: When the Rustbucket breaks down outside the largest mall in the U.S., it seems Ben and Gwen will have the time of their lives in the mall. That is until they run into an evil hypnotist entertaining the crowd, who puts Ben under hypnosis, causing him to sleepwalk at night and help him steal things. And when the hypnotist discovers certain aliens are now helping him, he exploits them for his grand plan of hypnotizing hundreds of people so they'll be under his demented control forever. Ben must figure out how to break the spell he's under and stop this evil plan.

added.title: A Change of Face
added.description: In Salem Massachusetts, Ben, Gwen and Max once again go up against Charmcaster, whose goal is to switch souls with Ben and possess the Omnitrix. However, Charmcaster first accidentally switches identities with Gwen, and then as spells fly back and forth, Ben and Gwen even end up in one another's bodies before they team up to get rid of Charmcaster once and for all.

added.title: The Secret of the Omnitrix Part 1
added.description: In a battle with Animo, Ben in hero mode, doesn't listen to reason from Max and Gwen, and gets engulfed in a weird energy light. Little does Ben know that the "self destruct" function on the Omnitrix has just been initiated!

added.title: Valentimes
added.description: When Clarence notices his teacher Ms. Baker is the only one in class left without a Valentine this year, he decides to enlist the help of Sumo to set her up with Sumo's teacher, Mr. Mozer! Will sparks fly or will the boy's naïve view of romance backfire?

added.title: Accion Roja al Futuro
added.description: Cuando convocan a Acción Roja a una batalla épica en el futuro, Enid no está segura de lo que debe hacer.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Collection Infection
added.description: Having pared down their Magisword collection, the Warriors are forced into unconventional battle choices on a dangerous mission into the Deepest Darkest Woods.

added.title: For the Love of Narwhal
added.description: Vambre rejects Darlin' Narwhal Magisword as being unfit for battle, but when Prohyas trains and brings out its full potential, Vambre resorts to improper extremes to get it back.

added.title: Suitable Armor
added.description: A veteran warrior insists that Vambre is under dressed for battle and takes it upon herself to garb Vambre in armor as Prohyas fights the beast solo without armor.

added.title: Dream Scheme/You Snooze, You Lose
added.description: Dream Scheme: The Sandman would like a little rest so he puts the world to sleep. The girls must battle him in his dreams to get things back to normal./You Snooze, You Lose: When the Amoeba Boys find Mojo's plan to destroy the Powerpuff Girls, the girls unwittingly help them build a machine for their own destruction.

added.title: Fixing a Flonk
added.description: Wanting to stop Flonk from being an evildoer for good, Prohyas tries to find Flonk a permanent venue for his nasty comedy. Vambre, however, wants to deliver him to the cops as usual.

added.title: Apointa a la Plaza
added.description: Cuando la plaza se infesta de pegote, P.O.I.N.T. llega para contener la situación.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Ain't That a Kick in the Side?
added.description: After Witch Way teases Prohyas by calling him, "Vambre's sidekick," Prohyas intensifies his efforts to prove them wrong.

added.title: Game Show
added.description: While shopping with his Mom, Clarence discovers Breehn hiding in a clothes rack. Under the guise of trying on new clothes for their moms, they sneak out to find a local gameshow being hosted inside the Aberdale Mall.

added.title: Mystery Girl
added.description: After Clarence and pals call random numbers as a prank, Clarence ends up connecting with a girl and they strike up a friendship. But will this long distance phone pal last?

added.title: Classroom
added.description: Over the course of a single day in Ms. Baker's class, we see how Clarence and his classmates deal with their individual trials during the school day.

added.title: Power Outage
added.description: A ghoul known as Calythos possesses the Parasite in order to drain the Justice League of its powers and use that stolen strength to open a massive volcano.

added.title: Pretty Great Day with a Girl
added.description: Clarence and Amy, a unique girl from down the street, bond over a hunt for a monster-sized rock called an "erratic."

added.title: Abate and Switch
added.description: When the JLA tries to stop the Brothers Djinn, the ghoulish trio are able to direct spells on our heroes by saying their names forcing them to disguise themselves as each other in order to foil the spells.

added.title: Nuclear Family Values
added.description: Firestorm encounters the Nuclear Family, a misguided group of robots who resemble a '50's sitcom family. They intend on blowing up a nuclear power plant in order to create a home where no one can touch them and they hope to use Firestorm's power to help them.

added.title: Galaxy Jest
added.description: Joker is abducted into space by Mongul to entertain Mongul's troops. Unless the Justice League can re-capture him in time, a Joker gas bomb will go off in Gotham threatening the city.

added.title: Under a Red Sun
added.description: Steppenwolf "boom tubes" Superman to a planet with a red sun in order to make the Man of Steel powerless. Somehow Batman and Big Barda have to locate the planet before Superman is destroyed.

added.title: The Frogs of War Part 2
added.description: With Ben missing, the Incurseans now control the Earth. It's up to Rook and the remaining Plumbers to lead the resistance and fight back! (Introducing new Ben alien, Bullfrag.)

added.title: The Ultimate Heist
added.description: Albedo seeks a device that will finally change him back into his Galvan form; meanwhile, Ben is locked in Plumber HQ prison.

added.title: Charmed, I'm Sure
added.description: Still stranded on the monster planet Anur Transyl, Ben and Rook reluctantly team up with Charmcaster to take on Zs' Skayr.

added.title: Cough It Up
added.description: Psyphon and a gang of bounty hunters are after Argit, who is in possession of a dangerous weapon!

added.title: Weapon XI Part 1
added.description: Kevin and Argit attempt to warn the amalgam kids about the Rooters intentions meanwhile Ben, Rook, and Gwen set off to find Kevin and land themselves in the Null Void!

added.title: Fishing Trip
added.description: Mel learns that Chad has never taken Clarence fishing, a tradition he sees as a rite of passage, and decides to remedy this with a bonding trip for all the boys! Split into two groups, Mel and Clarence learn a bit about each other while Chad struggles with the ins and outs of fishing.

added.title: Sumo Goes West
added.description: Clarence learns his best friend Sumo may transfer to another school! It's up to Clarence to protest, petition and rally to convince everyone to let Sumo stay - or face losing his closest school pal!

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: Fun Dungeon Face Off
added.description: Clarence's Mom treats Clarence, Jeff and Sumo to an afternoon at Rough Riders Chicken, a fast food restaurant with a play emporium. When Clarence and Sumo steal Jeff's fries, Jeff is forced to confront his germ phobias head-on in the restaurant's seemingly unsanitary play area.

added.title: Jeff's New Toy
added.description: Jeff wants to keep his new, flying "Wrath Hover Ginsbot" toy in its box. Clarence is desperate to play with the toy. And poor Sumo is caught in the middle.

added.title: Man of the House
added.description: Clarence's first night home alone spirals out of control, forcing Clarence and his pals to wage war against their own home security measures.

added.title: Get That BORFL!
added.description: A restful chill day for the Warriors and Princess Zange in the Royal Spa gets upended when a cute little Borfl runs amok throughout Castle Rhyboflaven, with the Warriors resorting to Magiswords to thwart the critter.

added.title: Letter Wronging Campaign
added.description: When Prohyas sends Vambre for a much needed spa day, he drafts Noville to help on a mission to discover why all the books in the Library of Shhhhh are blank.

added.title: Bad Heir Day
added.description: Princess Zange's Autostyle Magisword is stolen and it's up to the Warriors to retrieve it so their royal leader can face her subjects without bad hair.

added.title: School's In, Oh Bummer
added.description: It turns out that Vambre and Prohyas didn't graduate the Adventure Academy after all and need to go back to school earn their diplomas!

added.title: Quest for Knowledge
added.description: After a flashback where we learn the origins of the Warriors passion for Magiswords, they return to Adventure Academy where Professor Cyrus sets V and P and their former classmates on a quest to find the Legendary Knowledge Magisword.

added.title: Cumple De Bestia y Star
added.description: Chico Bestia acepta compartir su cumpleaños con Starfire al enterarse de que ella nunca celebró uno en la Tierra.

added.title: El Aguadios
added.description: Es el Cinco de Mayo, y Robin se entera de que los aguacates son un superalimento que da superpoderes.

added.title: Feliz Amiclumpleanos
added.description: Chico Bestia y Cyborg celebran el cumpleaños de su amistad.

added.title: Sabiduria, Fuerza y Carisma
added.description: Cuando Enid va a una escuela nueva, KO está decidido a asegurarse de que encaje.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Seamos Heroes
added.description: Cuando K.O. acompaña a su mamá al trabajo, descubre que la tienda de al lado es su clave para convertirse en un gran héroe.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Seamos Amigos
added.description: K.O. quiere hacerse amigo de Enid y Rad, y que lo contraten en Plaza Lakewood Turbo.
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol

added.title: Nos Equivocamos
added.description: iK.O., Rad y Enid rompen por accidente una de las preciadas posesiones del Sr. Gar!
added.originalseriesname: OK K.O.! Let's Be Heroes en Espanol
